The chatbot also said that retailers could only accept card payments, in fact violating a municipal law that from 2020 obliges businesses to accept cash payments. In another answer the chatbot did not appear even much &nbsp; added: he spoke of minimum hourly pay of 15 dollars, when from this year he climbed to 16.
&nbsp;
"There were mistakes - the mayor explained - but we solved them. "Every time you rely on technology - he added, speaking to journalists - you need to test it in real life to oil mechanisms."
