In fact, without the certainty of reliability it is advisable to stay away. Adams has always been a supporter of the use of untested technologies, but his optimism has not always been repaid by the results. Last year the mayor had authorized the use of a robot of nearly 200 kilos to help the police fight crime, but the experiment was blocked after just five months. Hundreds of commuters had reported how the robot stopped doing nothing all day and was unable to use the stairs.&nbsp;

